HEADWORD: Amir
<hw>A*mir"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Emir</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an
independent ruler or chieftan (especially in Africa or Arabia). Same as
<er>Emir</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> emir, amir, emeer</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the Muslim nobility of Afghanistan and
